100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 20, 1925, the League of Nations held discussions regarding the ongoing tensions in the Balkans, highlighting the fragile peace in Europe. In the United States, the Supreme Court delivered a significant ruling on the regulation of radio broadcasting, which could shape future communications. Meanwhile, in Chicago, local authorities announced plans to combat rising crime rates, promising increased police presence in troubled neighborhoods.
